Title: India to double CNG stations to 18,000 by 2030 amid One Nation, One Gas Grid plan: Puri

Title: China receives first Arctic LNG 2 cargo ahead of Putin's visit, data shows
China Takes LNG Cargo From US-Sanctioned Russian Facility
Description: A Chinese state-run terminal appeared to take delivery of some liquefied natural gas from a US-sanctioned Russian facility, according to shiptracking data, which would mark the first such trade as Moscow tries to maintain its energy exports.

Title: Technip Energies, JGC Win Abadi LNG FEED Contracts

Title: Gas Treatment, Liquefaction Units of Congo LNG Phase 2 Completed
Description: The second phase, which will raise the capacity of the Republic of the Congo's first LNG production facility to three MMtpa, is set to start operations by year-end.
